{"warnings":{"parse":{"*":"The value passed for \"page\" contains invalid or non-normalized data. Textual data should be valid, NFC-normalized Unicode without C0 control characters other than HT (\\t), LF (\\n), and CR (\\r)."}},"parse":{"title":"Cuesti\u00f3n moral: si el chocolate quebranta el ayuno eclesi\u00e1stico","pageid":48801464,"revid":846969132,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><caption style=\"font-style:italic;padding-bottom:0.2em;\">Cuesti\u00f3n Moral. Si el chocolate quebranta el ayuno eclesi\u00e1stico <span class=\"Z3988\" title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Cuesti%C3%B3n+Moral.+Si+el+chocolate+quebranta+el+ayuno+eclesi%C3%A1stico&amp;rft.author=Antonio+de+Le%C3%B3n+Pinelo\"></span></caption><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/File:Cuesti%C3%B3n_moral._Si_el_chocolate_quebranta_el_ayuno_eclesi%C3%A1stico,_Madrid,_1636.TIF\" class=\"image\" title=\"Cuesti\u00f3n moral. Si el chocolate quebranta el ayuno eclesi\u00e1stico, Madrid, 1636\"><img alt=\"Cuesti\u00f3n moral. Si el chocolate quebranta el ayuno eclesi\u00e1stico, Madrid, 1636\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bc/Cuesti%C3%B3n_moral._Si_el_chocolate_quebranta_el_ayuno_eclesi%C3%A1stico%2C_Madrid%2C_1636.TIF/lossy-page1-220px-Cuesti%C3%B3n_moral._Si_el_chocolate_quebranta_el_ayuno_eclesi%C3%A1stico%2C_Madrid%2C_1636.TIF.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"322\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bc/Cuesti%C3%B3n_moral._Si_el_chocolate_quebranta_el_ayuno_eclesi%C3%A1stico%2C_Madrid%2C_1636.TIF/lossy-page1-330px-Cuesti%C3%B3n_moral._Si_el_chocolate_quebranta_el_ayuno_eclesi%C3%A1stico%2C_Madrid%2C_1636.TIF.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bc/Cuesti%C3%B3n_moral._Si_el_chocolate_quebranta_el_ayuno_eclesi%C3%A1stico%2C_Madrid%2C_1636.TIF/lossy-page1-440px-Cuesti%C3%B3n_moral._Si_el_chocolate_quebranta_el_ayuno_eclesi%C3%A1stico%2C_Madrid%2C_1636.TIF.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1563\" data-file-height=\"2286\" /></a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Author</th><td>\nAntonio de Le\u00f3n Pinelo</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Original&#160;title</th><td>\n<i>Qvestion Moral. Si el chocolate quebranta el ayuno eclesi\u00e1stico</i></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Country</th><td>\nMexico</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><i><b>Cuesti\u00f3n moral: si el chocolate quebranta el ayuno eclesi\u00e1stico</b></i> (in English: <i>Whether chocolate breaks ecclesiastical fast: a moral question</i>) is a 1636 book written by the Spanish historian <a href=\"/wiki/Antonio_de_Le%C3%B3n_Pinelo\" title=\"Antonio de Le\u00f3n Pinelo\">Antonio de Le\u00f3n Pinelo</a> about the role of <a href=\"/wiki/List_of_chocolate_beverages\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"List of chocolate beverages\">chocolate beverages</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/Europe\" title=\"Europe\">European</a> society in the <a href=\"/wiki/17th_century\" title=\"17th century\">17th century</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-:0_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:0-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Cuesti%C3%B3n_moral:_si_el_chocolate_quebranta_el_ayuno_eclesi%C3%A1stico&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: History\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>This book was written during the 17th century, a time when <a href=\"/wiki/Chocolate\" title=\"Chocolate\">chocolate</a> became a very popular drink in <a href=\"/wiki/Spain\" title=\"Spain\">Spain</a>. The chocolate drink was introduced among the Mexican <a href=\"/wiki/Religious_order\" title=\"Religious order\">religious</a>, and later, in the highest social ranks of the European society. There were controversies at the time among the ecclesiastical authorities about the supposed stimulating effect of the beverage, thus its consumption in the churches was prohibited in 1681.<sup id=\"cite_ref-:0_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:0-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Content\">Content</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Cuesti%C3%B3n_moral:_si_el_chocolate_quebranta_el_ayuno_eclesi%C3%A1stico&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Content\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tleft\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Qvestion_Moral._Si_el_chocolate_quebranta_el_ayuno_eclesi%C3%A1stico.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/db/Qvestion_Moral._Si_el_chocolate_quebranta_el_ayuno_eclesi%C3%A1stico.jpg/220px-Qvestion_Moral._Si_el_chocolate_quebranta_el_ayuno_eclesi%C3%A1stico.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"164\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/db/Qvestion_Moral._Si_el_chocolate_quebranta_el_ayuno_eclesi%C3%A1stico.jpg/330px-Qvestion_Moral._Si_el_chocolate_quebranta_el_ayuno_eclesi%C3%A1stico.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/db/Qvestion_Moral._Si_el_chocolate_quebranta_el_ayuno_eclesi%C3%A1stico.jpg/440px-Qvestion_Moral._Si_el_chocolate_quebranta_el_ayuno_eclesi%C3%A1stico.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"3584\" data-file-height=\"2672\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Qvestion_Moral._Si_el_chocolate_quebranta_el_ayuno_eclesi%C3%A1stico.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><i>Cuesti\u00f3n Moral. Si el chocolate quebranta el ayuno eclesi\u00e1stico,</i> in the <a href=\"/wiki/Museo_Soumaya\" title=\"Museo Soumaya\">Museo Soumaya</a>'s collection.</div></div></div>\n<p>The book explores the temptations, fantasies and fears associated with the chocolate drink, a beverage that caused furor in <a href=\"/wiki/Madrid\" title=\"Madrid\">Madrid</a> at the beginning of the 17th century. The author explores different views on the same object of desire, chocolate, included the views of <a href=\"/wiki/Theology\" title=\"Theology\">theologists</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Morality\" title=\"Morality\">moralists</a> who had never tasted the beverage. This collection of opinions, often opposite and thus controversial, give the book its value.<sup id=\"cite_ref-:0_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:0-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Pinelo's work explored the role of the chocolate beverage at the time. According to Mexican historian Antonio Rubel Garc\u00eda, chocolate consumption was framed in a discussion between those who perceived the things brought from <a href=\"/wiki/Americas\" title=\"Americas\">the Americas</a> as \"decadent, putrid, imperfect\", and those who defended its virtues and beauty.<sup id=\"cite_ref-:1_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:1-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The book indicates the chocolate beverage was discovered by the <a href=\"/wiki/Pre-Columbian_era\" title=\"Pre-Columbian era\">pre-Hispanic</a> indigenous, who used it in their rituals and exclusively by their nobility and their priests. When the Spaniards adopted the chocolate beverage, they modified it by adding products such as <a href=\"/wiki/Sugar\" title=\"Sugar\">sugar</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Vanilla\" title=\"Vanilla\">vanilla</a>, and <a href=\"/wiki/Cinnamon\" title=\"Cinnamon\">cinnamon</a>, besides extending its consumption to all <a href=\"/wiki/Social_stratification\" title=\"Social stratification\">social stratums</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-:1_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:1-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Chocolate became a mechanism of socialization and festivity, thus triggering its prohibition within the <a href=\"/wiki/Carmelites\" title=\"Carmelites\">Carmelite</a> convents, where it was considered against the rules of <a href=\"/wiki/Christian_monasticism\" title=\"Christian monasticism\">monastic life</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-:1_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:1-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Mexican historian M. Merc\u00e8 Gras Casanova affirms chocolate drink was considered to be so extraordinary and exquisite that the religious authorities considered its consumption as a sin, because it was \"in the <a href=\"/wiki/Antipodes\" title=\"Antipodes\">antipodes</a> of the rigor and the <a href=\"/wiki/Asceticism\" title=\"Asceticism\">asceticism</a> pretended by any good <a href=\"/wiki/Christian\" title=\"Christian\">Christian</a>.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Cuesti%C3%B3n_moral:_si_el_chocolate_quebranta_el_ayuno_eclesi%C3%A1stico&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-:0-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-:0_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-:0_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-:0_1-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\"><i>Cuesti\u00f3n moral: Si el chocolate quebranta el ayuno eclesi\u00e1stico</i> &#91;<i>Whether chocolate breaks ecclesiastical fast: a moral question</i>&#93; (in Spanish). Mexico: Centro de Estudios de Historia de M\u00e9xico Carso. 2015. p.&#160;18.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;